oad PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533207\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533207\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vvw1665702871308.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vvw1665702871308.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vvw1665702871308.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vvw1665702871308\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Widget and Label Fonts\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"vvw1665702871308__widget_and_label_fonts_85502\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A font in Uniface has a logical name and a physical name. The physical font names are system-specific. The logical font names are mapped to their physical names in the initialization file for the GUI. You can specify the font to use for both the data displayed in a widget and the widget label.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvw1665702871308__p_d25493e1_d25494e1_d25495e1\">All widgets have the following font properties:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vvw1665702871308__li_d12626e1_d12627e1_d12628e1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Widget Font</span>—font used in the widget itself. For example, the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Widget Font</span> for a drop-down list determines the font that\n               Uniface uses for the items in the list itself. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvw1665702871308__p_d25496e1_d25497e1_d25498e1\">To ensure that the insertion character displays\n               correctly, make sure that the size of the widget font is less than or equal to the\n               size of the system font (Font 0).</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvw1665702871308__p_d25499e1_d25500e1_d25501e1\">If the widget font is larger than the available\n               space in the widget, the widget can behave unpredictably at runtime. For example,\n               Microsoft Windows hides the cursor and truncates the text at the bottom. To correct\n               this, choose a smaller font or enlarge the size of the widget. Alternatively, define\n               a bigger font for screen Font 0. This results in all forms appearing larger on the\n               screen.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vvw1665702871308__li_d12629e1_d12630e1_d12631e1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Label Font</span>—font used in the label associated with the widget.\n               For this definition to work, you must have associated the label with the widget, or\n               have loaded the label and widget via Load Fields. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvw1665702871308__p_d25502e1_d25503e1_d25504e1\">It is recommended that you specify the label font\n               for a widget in its properties, rather than in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span>\n               file.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533207\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533207\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Widget and Label Fonts Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Widget and Label Fonts A font in Uniface has a logical name and a physical name. The physical font names are system-specific. The logical font names are mapped to their physical names in the initialization file for the GUI. You can specify the font to use for both the data displayed in a widget and the widget label. All widgets have the following font properties: Widget Font —font used in the widget itself. For example, the Widget Font for a drop-down list determines the font that Uniface uses for the items in the list itself. To ensure that the insertion character displays correctly, make sure that the size of the widget font is less than or equal to the size of the system font (Font 0). If the widget font is larger than the available space in the widget, the widget can behave unpredictably at runtime. For example, Microsoft Windows hides the cursor and truncates the text at the bottom. To correct this, choose a smaller font or enlarge the size of the widget. Alternatively, define a bigger font for screen Font 0. This results in all forms appearing larger on the screen. Label Font —font used in the label associated with the widget. For this definition to work, you must have associated the label with the widget, or have loaded the label and widget via Load Fields. It is recommended that you specify the label font for a widget in its properties, rather than in the .ini file. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}